Notes:
  - `state` column is per-adapter freeform JSONB; e.g., googlesheets
    stores {"last_row_count": N}, gmail stores {"start_history_id": H},
    googlecalendar stores {"last_seen_updated": ISO}. The cron-kicker
    treats it as opaque — only the adapter knows the shape.
  - `consecutive_failures` + `paused_at` are the kicker's
    circuit-breaker. Plan: pause at 5 consecutive failures, emit
    composio_poll_paused activity event into the latest open run for
    the workspace. F.2 wires this.
  - We chose UNIQUE(automation_id, trigger_index) over a per-(toolkit,
    event) global unique because the same automation can legitimately
    have multiple triggers of the same toolkit (e.g., watch two
    sheets) at different indices.

Out of scope (lands in F.2):
  - The cron-kicker's poll_composio_triggers entry point
  - The adapter framework + registry
  - The EventBridge schedule that fires the kicker every minute
